                        <r3d:remarks>Description: The Terrorism and Preparedness Data Resource Center (TPDRC) archives and distributes data collected by government agencies, non-governmental organizations (NGOs), and researchers about the nature of intra- (domestic) and international terrorism incidents, organizations, perpetrators, and victims; governmental and nongovernmental responses to terror, including primary, secondary, and tertiary interventions; and citizen&#039;s attitudes towards terrorism, terror incidents, and the response to terror. The Terrorism and Preparedness Survey Archive (TaPSA) is part of the Terrorism &amp; Preparedness Data Resource Center (TPDRC).
TPDRC uses DDI metadata Standard. If you locate a membership-only study that fits your research needs and would like to purchase it, you can find more information about this process on the Nonmember Access to Data page.</r3d:remarks>
